## 🛡️ Implementing the Compensating Control (The FIM Pivot)

Faced with a complete lack of behavioral process logs (due to the Sysmon failure), I transitioned the defensive strategy to an event-driven asset protection framework using **Wazuh File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)**. 

I modified the administrative configuration profile (`ossec.conf`) on the endpoint to bind real-time file hooks to a dedicated lab folder:

<directories realtime="yes" check_all="yes">C:\Lab-FIM</directories>

* **`realtime="yes"`**: Leverages instant OS filesystem notifications (`ReadDirectoryChangesW`) to bypass standard periodic scanning intervals, shipping telemetry immediately upon file creation.
* **`check_all="yes"`**: Mandates the immediate computation and tracking of file size, local permissions, owner attributes, and multiple cryptographic hash standards (MD5, SHA1, SHA256).

