## 💥 Adversary Simulation Phase (Red Team Action)

To validate the compensating control, I simulated an endpoint compromise scenario by dropping the weaponized binary `mimikatz.exe` into the monitored directory path (`C:\Lab-FIM\mimikatz.exe`).

The utility was then initiated from an administrative shell to simulate an interactive local credential-harvesting attempt:

powershell
cd C:\Lab-FIM
.\mimikatz.exe
sekurlsa::logonpasswords

Even when local OS restrictions blocked the internal LSASS memory dump, the deployment objective was to test the SIEM's capability to ingest and identify the threat actor's toolkit static footprint.

